<h2>Conquer Chứa Chan Mountain</h2>
<p><b>Chua Chan Mountain is known as the second highest mountain in the Southeast region with many steep cliffs, diverse ecosystems... Because it is located not far from Saigon, this place is often loved by many young people. and choose to explore.</b></p><br>
 <p>About 100 km from Saigon, along Highway 1A towards Dong Nai, Chua Chan Mountain also has many other names such as Gia Ray Mountain or Gia Lao Mountain in Xuan Loc district, Dong Nai province. This is the second highest mountain in the South (after Ba Den Mountain - Tay Ninh) with an altitude of 837 m above sea level. Chua Chan Mountain has a majestic landscape and is considered the headland of Dong Nai province, the origin of many streams (Gia Ui stream flows to the east, Gia Mien stream flows to the west, Gia Lieu stream flows to the south and Gia Lao stream flowing north) with fresh, cool water all year round. In the rock cavities, there are water veins that extrude and stagnate into small lakes, which local people call Fairy wells.</p>
 <img class="img6" src="{{asset('blog/files/chuachan1.jpg')}}" alt="núi chứa chan">
<p>In particular, coming to Chua Chan Mountain, visitors can also visit one of the pagodas located halfway up the mountain in the relic cluster - Buu Quang Pagoda (also known as Gia Lao Pagoda). This is the most famous and sacred temple because it has no merit box and was built based on the natural terrain of the mountains and forests. In front is a 3-root Da tree about 30m high, formed from three roots. bunched together to create a very strange and mysterious shape. People often call this the Da Tree with 3 roots and 1 top associated with mystical stories and is considered a sacred place attracting many tourists to pray for peace, fortune, and fortune.</p><br>
<p>There are many ways to explore this mountain, such as going in the direction of the temple. But according to the experience of backpackers climbing Gia Lao mountain, it is easier to follow the electric pole path to reach the top of the mountain. The high mountain slope in the north of Xuan Truong commune has many rocks stuck into thick walls, with deep, winding entrances. This rocky area was designated by relic ranking agencies as Ham Hinh Secret Area because it is associated with the period when revolutionary forces used it as a base during the fight against the French and Americans.</p><br>
<p>The beautiful time on Chua Chan mountain, when the sun has not yet fully risen, is when the color of the sky becomes more brilliant with an extremely strange pink-purple color. Until the sun gradually rose, the space became brighter and the whole scene gradually became clearer. There is no longer any black space in front of us, everything becomes brighter and clearer. The sky was also higher and clearer, the bright yellow sun had risen and dyed the whole space yellow.</p><br>

<p>A place with many beautiful landscapes like Chua Chan Mountain, especially Chua Chan Mountain has been ranked as a national scenic relic by the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism. On the mountain there is the Ham Hinh secret area and the French governor's guest house, Buu Quang pagoda, Lam Son Tu, Linh Son Tu... The climate is cool, nature is gentle with rich flora and fauna. With local efforts, Chua Chan Mountain will be a tourist destination worth stopping in Dong Nai in particular and the Southeast region in general.</p><br>



